#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:3
msgid "Normalization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:5
msgid ""
"Traffic normalization protects internal machines against inconsistencies "
"in Internet protocols and implementations. OPNsense has some generic "
"options to normalize some packets on a per interface basis, in some cases"
" more detailed changes are needed, for which custom rules can be "
"configured."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:9
msgid ""
"By default (when **Disable interface scrub** is not set), all interfaces "
"are scrubbed for all traffic, with :code:`fragment reassemble` enabled "
"and :code:`max-mss` set when specified in **MSS** on the interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:14
msgid ""
"Some protocols, such as NFS, require specific fragment handling options, "
"which my require specific options set like **IP Do-Not-Fragment***"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:20
msgid "Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:22
msgid ""
"Normalization rules use the same kind of matching as normal firewall "
"rules, which we are not going to detail here. When matched, some "
"different options can be set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:28
msgid ""
"When rules overlap, the first matching rule wins, hence per interface "
"options are sorted after user configurable ones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:35
msgid "Max mss"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:35
msgid ""
"Enforces a maximum MSS for matching TCP packets. Can also be configured "
"on the interface as general rule."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:37
msgid "TOS / DSCP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:37
msgid "Enforces a TOS/DCP for matching IP packets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:38
msgid "Minimum TTL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:38
msgid "Enforces a minimum TTL for matching IP packets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:39
msgid "Do not fragment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:39
msgid ""
"Clears the :code:`dont-fragment` bit for a matching IP packet, which "
"disables `IP fragmentation "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IP_fragmentation>`__ when set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:42
msgid "Random ID"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/firewall_scrub.rst:42
msgid ""
"Replaces the IP identification field with random values to compensate for"
" predictable values generated by many hosts. This option only applies to "
"packets that are not fragmented after the optional fragment reassembly."
msgstr ""

